\cf2 \cb3 This Bagurumba dance is originated from nature. Some thousands of years ago it was practiced by the \cf4 Boro people\cf2 . Generally Boro people like to stay in a green environment. They love to play with the environment, beauty of nature. So they used to stay in the foothills of the eastern and southern Himalayas, which are generally forest area. There are so many different symbols in this traditional dance, which are imitated from other natural environment. Like \'96 dance of plants, dance of animals, birds, butterfly dance, wave of flowing river, wind etc.\cb1 \
\cb3 By seeing this bagurumba dance, all Boro people can\'92t stay calm and quiet. By seeing this dance, suddenly every Bodo people use to dance unknowingly, and they feel peace and happiness in their mind.\cb1 \
\cb3 There are no certain days and times to perform this dance; this dance can be performed on any occasion, festival and programme. At present Bagurumba dance is famous over the whole world.\cb1 \
